        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 6:38PM EDT by NWS Buffalo NY</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM EDT, a line of heavy rain was located near Lockport,
producing rainfall rates of up to one inch per hour. This line will
shift slowly northward through 730 PM. Before it does, it may result
in ponding of water on roadways, and rises on small creeks and
streams. Localized flooding is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gasport, Cambria Center, Lewiston, Pendleton Center, Lockport,
Middleport, Wolcottsville, Sanborn, Model City, and Rapids.
</description>
